draw((-1,4)--(6,4));
draw((-1,3)--(6,3));
draw((-1,2)--(6,2));
draw((-1,1)--(6,1));
draw((0,-1)--(0,6));
draw((-1,5)--(6,5));
draw((-1,0)--(6,0));
draw((5,-1)--(5,6));
</asy>
We can now count the number of black and white tiles; 32 black tiles and 17 white tiles. This means the answer is <math>\boxed{\textbf{(D) }32:17}</math>.

