A=dir(45);
B=dir(90);
C=dir(135);
D=dir(180);
E=dir(-135);
F=dir(-90);
G=dir(-45);
H=dir(0);
O=(0,0);
X=midpoint(A--B);
a=midpoint(B--C);
b=midpoint(C--D);
c=midpoint(D--E);
d=midpoint(E--F);
e=midpoint(F--G);
f=midpoint(G--H);
g=midpoint(H--A);

fill(X--B--C--D--E--O--cycle,rgb(0.75,0.75,0.75));
draw(A--B--C--D--E--F--G--H--cycle);

dot("$A$",A,dir(45));
dot("$B$",B,dir(90));
dot("$C$",C,dir(135));
dot("$D$",D,dir(180));
dot("$E$",E,dir(-135));
dot("$F$",F,dir(-90));
dot("$G$",G,dir(-45));
dot("$H$",H,dir(0));
dot("$X$",X,dir(135/2));
dot("$O$",O,dir(0));
draw(E--O--X);
draw(B--F);
draw(A--O);
draw(D--H);
draw(C--G);
draw(a--e);
draw(b--f);
draw(c--g);
draw(d--O);
</asy>

The octagon has been divided up into <math>16</math> identical triangles (and thus they each have equal area). Since the shaded region occupies <math>7</math> out of the <math>16</math> total triangles, the answer is <math>\boxed{\textbf{(D)}~\dfrac{7}{16}}</math>.

-Flare

===Solution 3===

For starters, what I find helpful is to divide the whole octagon up into triangles as shown here:
<asy>
